  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Apricot Grilling Sauce Base</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Sauces</cat>
        <cat>Bbq &amp; grill</cat></categories>
      <yield>1</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>16</qty>
          <unit>ounces</unit></amt>
        <item>Apricot halves</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Chopped onion</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Cloves garlic; finely chopped</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Vegetable oil</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Salt</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/4</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Pepper</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  To make the grilling sauce base, puree apricot haves with their liquid in a
  blender or food processor; reserve. Saute onion and garlic in oil until
  translucent. Stir in reserved apricot puree.
  
  Yields 2 1/2 cups.
  
  (From California Canned Apricots)
  
